                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;This is fantastic - nice one @bluefeet. I&apos;d never used &lt;code&gt;STUFF(...)&lt;/code&gt; before (or the &lt;code&gt;XML PATH&lt;/code&gt; either). For the benefit of other readers, all that is doing is joining the column names and chopping off the leading comma.  Note I think the following is slightly simpler:      select @cols =(SELECT DISTINCT QUOTENAME(Week) + &apos;,&apos;                          from yt                         order by 1                 FOR XML PATH(&apos;&apos;))     		     set @cols = SUBSTRING(@cols, 1, LEN(@cols) - 1)  ... replacing the &lt;code&gt;group by&lt;/code&gt; by &lt;code&gt;distinct&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;order by 1&lt;/code&gt; and manually chopping a &lt;i&gt;suffixed&lt;/i&gt; comma!&lt;/span&gt;

